<h1>Welcome to SOHC4shop.com</h1> 

<div class="contentContainer">
  <div class="contentText">
    Welcome <span class="greetUser">Guest!</span> Would you like to <a href="login.php?osCsid=9aebce0777e9593c6d90f6c0e7b5ad07"><u>log yourself in</u></a>? Or would you prefer to <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20220414001444/http://sohc4shop.com/catalog/create_account.php?osCsid=9aebce0777e9593c6d90f6c0e7b5ad07"><u>create an account</u></a>?  </div>


  <div class="contentText">
    SOHC4shop is not a "store" in the usual sense, but a place where one may find the parts, repairs, and assistance needed to put these great bikes back on the road. SOHC4shop is a hobby and a service for those who wish to ride these vintage bikes. <br><br> Most items seen herein are not "stocked items", but are available upon request, often with some reasonable delivery time required for their construction.<br><br>Please email inquiries to info@sohc4shop or webmaster@sohc4shop.  </div>
